The real difference

Training (foundational change)
	•	Happens inside the model
	•	Updates weights / parameters
	•	Requires:
	•	massive datasets
	•	compute (GPUs, clusters)
	•	optimization loops

Think:

changing the engine itself

⸻

Tuning (behavior shaping)
	•	Happens on top of the model
	•	Doesn’t change core weights (in your case)
	•	Uses:
	•	prompts
	•	constraints
	•	examples
	•	interaction patterns

Think:

learning how to drive the engine precisely

